x4freetext: Scattered neutrons were detected using five
NE213 scintillation detectors positioned at a
distance of 12 m from the sample behind a massive
collimator system. Sixth neutron detector served
.The elastic and inelastic cross sections were deter-
mined by comparing simulated TOF spectra with the
cross section used for the simulations were iterati-
vely adjusted until satisfactory agreement between
calculated and measured TOF spectra was achieved.
